n tags using `validate:` struct tags\n34: - [ ] Create `types/response.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`\n35: - [ ] Define `SandboxResponse` struct\n36: - [ ] Define `ListSandboxesResponse` struct\n37: - [ ] Add JSON tags using camelCase naming\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Task 3: Define Sandbox Configuration\n42: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/config/config.go` exists\n43: \n44: - [ ] Create `config/config.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`\n45: - [ ] Define `Config` struct with sandbox settings\n46: - [ ] Define `ResourceQuota` struct\n47: - [ ] Add default values using struct tags\n48: - [ ] Add JSON tags for configuration fields\n49: - [ ] Add struct documentation comments\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## Task 4: Define Sandbox Service Interface\n54: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/service/service.go` exists with interface\n55: \n56: - [ ] Create `service/service.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`\n57: - [ ] Define `SandboxService` interface\n58: - [ ] Add `CreateSandbox` method signature\n59: - [ ] Add `GetSandbox` method signature\n60: - [ ] Add `ListSandboxes` method signature\n61: - [ ] Add `DeleteSandbox` method signature\n62: - [ ] Add `UpdateStatus` method signature\n63: - [ ] Add `CheckQuota` method signature\n64: - [ ] Add package-level interface documentation\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## Task 5: Define Sandbox-Specific Errors\n69: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/errors/errors.go` exists\n70: \n71: - [ ] Create `errors/errors.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`\n72: - [ ] Define quota exceeded error\n73: - [ ] Define sandbox not found error\n74: - [ ] Define sandbox already exists error\n75: - [ ] Define invalid status transition error\n76: - [ ] Add error constructor functions\n77: - [ ] Add error checking helpers\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Task 6: Implement Quota Manager\n82: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/service/quota.go` exists and enforces limits\n83: \n84: