{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847215190,"sessionID":"ses_28743eb88ffeRh7ZR1ZU9lE1SN","part":{"id":"prt_d78bc7ae8001V9jCG59Edblb7S","messageID":"msg_d78bc4a37001mKLiLMXNsOzOgq","sessionID":"ses_28743eb88ffeRh7ZR1ZU9lE1SN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md","content":"# AR-005 Tasks: Sandbox 创建处理器 (Sandbox Creation Processor)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Create Core Data Types\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/types/request.go` and `pkg/workloadmanager/types/response.go` updated with sandbox types\n\n- [ ] Add `CreateSandboxRequest` struct with fields: Kind, Name, Namespace\n- [ ] Implement `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` method\n  - Verify test: returns error when Kind is empty or invalid\n  - Verify test: returns error when Name is empty\n  - Verify test: returns error when Namespace is empty\n  - Verify test: returns nil for valid request\n- [ ] Add `CreateSandboxResponse` struct with fields: SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints\n- [ ] Add `SandboxEntryPoint` struct with fields: Path, Protocol, Endpoint\n- [ ] Add `SandboxInfo` struct for Store persistence\n- [ ] Verify all structs have proper JSON tags (camelCase)\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/types/... -v -run \"TestCreateSandboxRequest\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Implement Workload Builder - Sandbox Object Construction\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with `buildSandboxObject()` function\n\n- [ ] Create `workload_builder.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `buildSandboxObject(runtime *AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n  - Generate sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n  - Set APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n  - Set Kind: `Sandbox`\n  - Add required labels (session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by)\n  - Add annotations (idle-timeout)\n  - Copy podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n  - Set replicas to 1\n  - Set lifecycle.shutdownTime\n- [ ] Write unit tests in `workload_builder_test.go`\n  - Verify test: sandbox name format is correct\n  - Verify test: all required labels are present\n  - Verify test: podTemplate is correctly copied\n  - Verify test: returns error when Template is nil\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestBuildSandboxObject\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Implement Workload Builder - SandboxClaim Object Construction\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with `buildSandboxClaimObject()` function\n\n- [ ] Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject(runtime *CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n  - Set APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n  - Set Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n  - Generate claim name with 8-char random suffix\n  - Add minimal metadata (session-id, workload-name labels)\n- [ ] Write unit tests in `workload_builder_test.go`\n  - Verify test: SandboxClaim has correct APIVersion and Kind\n  - Verify test: name follows expected format\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestBuildSandboxClaimObject\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Implement Workload Builder - CodeInterpreter Sandbox Construction\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with CodeInterpreter full sandbox support\n\n- [ ] Implement `buildCodeInterpreterSandbox(runtime *CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`\n  - Single container named \"code-interpreter\"\n  - Image from `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate.Image`\n  - Support AuthMode: inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var when authMode=picod\n  - Handle optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n  - Default ports: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if spec.Ports is empty\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: container name is \"code-interpreter\"\n  - Verify test: default port 8080 is used when Ports empty\n  - Verify test: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY injected when authMode=picod\n  - Verify test: no auth env var when authMode=none\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandbox\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Implement Pod IP Resolution\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with `resolvePodIP()` function\n\n- [ ] Implement `resolvePodIP(ctx, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName) (string, error)`\n  - First check `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` annotation\n  - Try informer cache lookup by pod name\n  - Fallback: list pods by `SandboxNameLabelKey` label\n  - Match pod by OwnerReference (Kind=Sandbox, Name=sandboxName)\n  - Return error if pod not in Running phase or PodIP is empty\n- [ ] Write unit tests with fake pod lister\n  - Verify test: resolves IP from annotation\n  - Verify test: resolves IP by sandbox name\n  - Verify test: resolves IP by OwnerReference\n  - Verify test: returns error when pod not running\n  - Verify test: returns error when no matching pod found\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestResolvePodIP\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: Implement EntryPoint Builder\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` with `buildEntryPoints()` function\n\n- [ ] Implement `buildEntryPoints(podIP string, ports []TargetPort) []SandboxEntryPoint`\n  - Map each port to SandboxEntryPoint\n  - Endpoint format: `{podIP}:{port}`\n  - Protocol from port.Protocol (HTTP/HTTPS)\n  - Path from port.PathPrefix\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: single port produces single entrypoint\n  - Verify test: multiple ports produce multiple entrypoints\n  - Verify test: endpoint format is correct\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestBuildEntryPoints\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 7: Implement Sandbox Creator Core\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` with `sandboxCreator` struct\n\n- [ ] Create `sandbox_creator.go` file\n- [ ] Define `sandboxCreator` struct with fields:\n  - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n  - `sandboxController *SandboxReconciler`\n  - `storeClient store.Store`\n  - `publicKey []byte`\n- [ ] Implement `NewSandboxCreator(k8sClient, controller, store, publicKey)` constructor\n- [ ] Write unit tests with mock dependencies\n  - Verify test: sandboxCreator is properly initialized\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestNewSandboxCreator\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 8: Implement Sandbox Creation Flow\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` with `createSandbox()` method\n\n- [ ] Implement `createSandbox(ctx, sandbox, isWarmPool, userClient) (*SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Step 1: Register watcher via `WatchSandboxOnce()` BEFORE creating CR\n  - Step 2: Create placeholder Store record with status \"pending\"\n  - Step 3: Create CR via dynamic client\n  - Step 4: Wait for running status (max 2 minutes timeout)\n  - Step 5: Resolve Pod IP and build EntryPoints\n  - Step 6: Update Store record with full info and status \"running\"\n  - Handle rollback on any failure\n- [ ] Write unit tests with mocked watcher and store\n  - Verify test: successful creation flow\n  - Verify test: rollback on timeout\n  - Verify test: rollback on IP resolution failure\n  - Verify test: Store placeholder created before CR\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestCreateSandbox\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 9: Implement Rollback Logic\n**Verifiable Output:** Rollback executed correctly on creation failures\n\n- [ ] Implement rollback in `createSandbox()`:\n  - CR creation before Store: delete Store record\n  - Timeout after CR creation: delete CR (30s timeout) + delete Store record\n  - IP resolution failure: delete CR + delete Store record\n  - Store update failure: log warning, CR left for GC\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: Store record deleted when CR creation fails\n  - Verify test: CR and Store deleted on timeout\n  - Verify test: CR and Store deleted on IP resolution failure\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestCreateSandboxRollback\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 10: Implement AgentRuntime Create Handler\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` with `handleAgentRuntimeCreate()` handler\n\n- [ ] Add `handleAgentRuntimeCreate(c *gin.Context)` handler\n  - Parse JSON body into `CreateSandboxRequest`\n  - Return 400 for JSON parse errors\n  - Force set `Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - Call `Validate()`, return 400 on validation failure\n  - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n  - Return 404 if not found\n  - Return 400 if podTemplate missing\n  - Call `createSandbox()`\n  - Return 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse` on success\n  - Return 500 for internal errors\n- [ ] Write unit tests in `handlers_test.go`\n  - Verify test: returns 200 on success\n  - Verify test: returns 400 for invalid JSON\n  - Verify test: returns 400 for missing name/namespace\n  - Verify test: returns 404 for non-existent runtime\n  - Verify test: returns 400 for missing podTemplate\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 11: Implement CodeInterpreter Create Handler\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` with `handleCodeInterpreterCreate()` handler\n\n- [ ] Add `handleCodeInterpreterCreate(c *gin.Context)` handler\n  - Similar to AgentRuntime handler\n  - Force set `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`\n  - Check `WarmPoolSize` to determine Sandbox vs SandboxClaim\n  - Handle AuthMode for publicKey injection\n  - Return appropriate status codes\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: returns 200 on success\n  - Verify test: creates SandboxClaim when WarmPoolSize > 0\n  - Verify test: creates full Sandbox when WarmPoolSize = 0\n  - Verify test: handles AuthMode=picod correctly\n  - Verify test: handles AuthMode=none correctly\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 12: Implement Idempotency Check\n**Verifiable Output:** Duplicate requests return same sessionId\n\n- [ ] Add idempotency check in create handlers\n  - Before creating, check Store for existing session with same workload name\n  - If exists and not expired, return existing sessionId\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: duplicate request returns same sessionId\n  - Verify test: new request after expiry creates new session\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestIdempotency\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 13: Implement Sandbox Controller Watcher\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` with `WatchSandboxOnce()` method\n\n- [ ] Create `sandbox_controller.go` file\n- [ ] Define `SandboxReconciler` struct with watcher registry\n- [ ] Implement `WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name) (chan struct{}, error)`\n  - Register one-time watcher for sandbox status change\n  - Return channel that closes when sandbox enters running state\n- [ ] Write unit tests\n  - Verify test: watcher returns channel\n  - Verify test: channel closes when sandbox becomes running\n  - Verify test: multiple watchers for same sandbox work independently\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -run \"TestWatchSandboxOnce\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 14: Implement GVR Constants and Defaults\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` with constants\n\n- [ ] Create `defaults.